Wittgenstein-late: appeal and readability as forms-of-life the audience shares — good animation speaks the language the audience knows.
Peirce: staging as symbol (compositional convention) plus icon (visual resemblance) plus index (physical trace of the animator's hand).
Not name-dropped.\"

